            <h2>
                   <strong> Scholarship Description:</strong>
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        Siemens Scholarship Program  is an initiative of Siemens India to support 1st year engineering students from the streams Mechanical/Production, Electrical,
                        Electronics/Instrumentation, Electronics and Telecommunication, Computers/Information Technology, Instrumentation.
                        The objective of this scholarship is to support determined students who are having devotion and perseverance towards learning.
                        The scholars can also be placed in the Siemens in various sectors in the coming future.
                        This scholarship will support the students to achieve their personal and professional goals.
                        


                           </p>
                            <h2>
                                <hr>
                                    <strong>Who can apply:</strong>
                                    </h2>
 <p>
 

<ul>
<li>Be a first-year student of Government Engineering colleges</li>
<li>Be below 20 years of age </li>
<li>Have scored at least 60% marks in class 10 board exams</li>
<li>Have scored 60% marks in PCM </li>
<li>Belongs to the family where annual income is not more than INR 2 lakhs</li>

</ul>
</p>
<h2>
    <hr>How to apply</strong>
</h2>
<p>
    <pre>
Interested candidate can apply online by following the below-mentioned steps:
Step 1: Go to the website
Step 2: Fill all the three sections of the form, (personal details, educational details, engineering details)
Step 3: The applicant has to select if currently availing any other scholarship or not
Step 4: The applicant has to select if availing hostel services or not
Step 5: Finally accept the terms and conditions and submit the form
</pre>
</p>
<h2>
    <hr>
    <strong>Benefits</strong>
</h2>
<p>
The scholarship will be disbursed annually and it comprises of:
Tuition fees reimbursement (In case if the student is availing any other scholarship, the balance tuition fee would be reimbursed)
Allowances on books, stationery, hostel, additional classes would be given
Holistic development program

</p>
                                                
       
